3:
"Gather the dragons for the sword of
light."
5:
In other words, dragons were
nothing but fodder for the
Champions.
6:
With every star destroyed, the
dragons were used and tossed
aside—only to be reborn and used
again, losing their memories in the
process.
8:
To escape this cruel cycle,
Armadeus traveled to the
abandoned world of Pandemonium
and discovered a way to defy his
fate.
11:
It was the power to overcome death
and allow one to pursue their
dreams—the one people called the
curse.
16:
The curse? Isn't that what created
daemons—
20:
Armadeus was a kindred soul. An...
accomplice, you could say.
23:
He drowned himself in rage and
hatred throughout many years and
many lives. He became a monster.
26:
I found his tormented form to be
marvelous...
29:
But the Lord of Shadow betrayed
him.
33:
He killed Armadeus and smashed
the Curse Crystal into countless
pieces. Perhaps he wanted his Mark.
41:
I gathered the pieces of the
shattered Curse Crystal. All I needed
was to join it to the curse.
44:
But somehow, the pieces of the
crystal scattered and vanished. As
for why, I have my suspicions, but
that isn't important at the moment.
47:
Won't you give me the last piece? It's
the only way to save that pitiful
dragon.
55:
What... will happen to Rooma if you
do that?
59:
Do you know what it takes to
connect the pieces of a shattered
memory?
62:
Imagination. The intelligence to link
separate pieces of information. To
dream.
65:
Rooma was a personality made for
that purpose. It isn't Armadeus.
73:
So what? That doesn't mean he
deserves to go away!
77:
Well, I suppose that means I'll have
to take it by force.
83:
Ahahaha! What a way to make an
entrance!
87:
Fool! Didst thou truly believe such
imperfect imitations could stand
against the original?
92:
...Their battle prowess was clearly
lacking. Apologies, Arma. I really did
wish to meet you one more time.
95: It's time to switch to plan B.
106:
Haha, to think it could even stop
ancient dragons in their tracks!
Perhaps I underestimated its value.
111:
What the hell are you trying to pull
now?!
115:
Isn't it obvious? I'm allowing the
device to function as intended.
118:
A dragon serves as prey for a
Champion.
121:
Put another way, this means that a
Champion should be the one to
prey upon a dragon.
133:
Yes... Who better than a soldier
made by the gods to purge the
world? Although this one is more of
a pirated version.
136:
Dragon Eater! Crush this star
beneath your heel!
143:
Stars above. Turn your cold
countenances. Upon the creatures
below. Who beg scraps. Of your
heavenly light.
166: Sorry, Barrek! Taiga! I'm using it now!
177:
So you can call down the stars, huh?
I've just about had it with that crap!
181: This is how a warrior really fights!
189: Pirate lady! You gonna help or what?!
205:
Czarina! We're directing all the
energy from the ship to you! Go wild!
208: We took the limiter off too!
211:
All right! I've always wanted to give
this a try!
224:
You know what it means to be a
Champion?
231:
It's to bear the burden of the
treasure I can't help but want!
234:
Just like that fluffy Champion of ours
does!
248:
We can't pull off those attacks
again! It's now or never!
259:
Couette, it's the job of a pirate to
take her treasure.
297:
That's what I'm talking about! Now
all we've gotta do is—
